text: Nathan Simeon (born February 14, 2000) is a Canadian soccer player who plays as a defender for the University of San Francisco. == Career == Simeon began his career by accepting a scholarship to join Orlando City's Club Development Academy system at Montverde Academy for the 2018–19 season. He made 14 appearances in his debut year. On March 30, 2019, Simeon signed an academy contract with Orlando City's USL reserve affiliate OCB and made his senior debut in the season opener later that day, a 3–1 loss to FC Tucson. In July 2019, Simeon verbally committed to play NCAA Division I soccer at the University of San Francisco. == References == == External links == * * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian soccer players Category:Canadian expatriate soccer players Category:Canadian expatriates in the United States Category:Association football defenders Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States Category:Orlando City B players Category:Soccer people from Quebec Category:Sportspeople from Montreal Category:USL League One players Category:San Francisco Dons men's soccer players
